layers.nm: Neuroscientists tracked bats exploring an island to uncover how their brains encode a sense of direction.

s.t: Neuroscientists tracked bats exploring an island to uncover how their brains encode a sense of direction.

layers.nm: Neurons known as head direction cells are connected in a ringlike network that is always active. The cells anchor themselves to landmarks; as the animal turns to face a new direction, different cells activate.
